   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# Readability Scoring Notebook\\n\",\"**NLP Project 19 of 100** — Estimate reading difficulty of text using Flesch-Kincaid, Gunning Fog, and other metrics.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\"1. Implement readability formulas from scratch.\\n\",\"2. Compare scores across different text types.\\n\",\"3. Understand syllable counting and sentence detection.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import re, numpy as np, pandas as pd, matplotlib.pyplot as plt, seaborn as sns\\nimport warnings; warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\\nsns.set_style('whitegrid')\\n%matplotlib inline\\nprint('Loaded.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"def count_syllables(word):\\n    word = word.lower().strip()\\n    if len(word) <= 2: return 1\\n    word = re.sub(r'e$', '', word)\\n    vowels = re.findall(r'[aeiouy]+', word)\\n    return max(1, len(vowels))\\n\\ndef readability_metrics(text):\\n    sentences = re.split(r'[.!?]+', text)\\n    sentences = [s.strip() for s in sentences if len(s.strip()) > 3]\\n    words = re.findall(r'\\\\b\\\\w+\\\\b', text)\\n    n_sent = max(1, len(sentences))\\n    n_words = max(1, len(words))\\n    syllables = sum(count_syllables(w) for w in words)\\n    complex_words = sum(1 for w in words if count_syllables(w) >= 3)\\n    # Flesch Reading Ease\\n    fre = 206.835 - 1.015*(n_words/n_sent) - 84.6*(syllables/n_words)\\n    # Flesch-Kincaid Grade\\n    fkg = 0.39*(n_words/n_sent) + 11.8*(syllables/n_words) - 15.59\\n    # Gunning Fog\\n    fog = 0.4*((n_words/n_sent) + 100*(complex_words/n_words))\\n    return {'sentences':n_sent,'words':n_words,'syllables':syllables,\\n            'flesch_ease':round(fre,1),'flesch_grade':round(fkg,1),'gunning_fog':round(fog,1)}\\n\\nprint('Functions ready.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"texts = {\\n    'Children\\\\'s Book': 'The cat sat on the mat. The dog ran fast. It was a nice day. They played in the park.',\\n    'News Article': 'The Federal Reserve announced a quarter-point interest rate increase. Analysts expect continued monetary tightening through the year. Markets reacted negatively.',\\n    'Academic Paper': 'The methodology employs a novel approach to multivariate statistical analysis incorporating heteroscedasticity-consistent covariance matrix estimation for longitudinal observational studies.',\\n    'Legal Document': 'Notwithstanding any provision herein to the contrary, the indemnifying party shall hold harmless and defend the indemnified party against all claims arising from negligent performance.',\\n}\\n\\nresults = []\\nfor name, text in texts.items():\\n    m = readability_metrics(text)\\n    m['Text Type'] = name\\n    results.append(m)\\n    print(f'{name}: Flesch Ease={m[\\\"flesch_ease\\\"]}, Grade={m[\\\"flesch_grade\\\"]}, Fog={m[\\\"gunning_fog\\\"]}')\\n\\nresults_df = pd.DataFrame(results)\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10,5))\\nresults_df.plot(x='Text Type',y=['flesch_ease','flesch_grade','gunning_fog'],kind='bar',ax=ax)\\nax.set_title('Readability Scores by Text Type'); ax.tick_params(axis='x',rotation=30)\\nplt.tight_layout(); plt.show()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Summary\\n\",\"- **Flesch Reading Ease**: Higher = easier. Children's books score 80+, legal docs score below 30.\\n\",\"- **Flesch-Kincaid Grade**: US grade level needed to understand the text.\\n\",\"- **Gunning Fog**: Similar to FK grade but weights complex words differently.\\n\",\"- **These metrics help writers target the right audience level.**\"]}\n",
    " ],\n",
